[2026-03-19T08:15:10.359Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016Z8Zfb9zE11mbrYEpYpUd2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No type errors in the modified files (the pre-existing errors are all in `oauth.ts`/`oauthHttpHandlers.ts`, unrelated to this change).\n\n**What was implemented:**\n\n1. **`TenantDbManager.getHealthStats()`** (`tenantDbManager.ts:71-128`) — New method that iterates all tenant databases and collects:\n   - **File size** via `PRAGMA page_count * page_size` (includes system DB + all tenant DBs)\n   - **Row counts** for `persona_executions` and `persona_events` tables\n   - **Oldest un-purged record age** across all tenants\n   - Per-tenant breakdown for drill-down\n\n2. **Periodic health log** (`index.ts:170-196`) — Added to the existing 60s status interval, logs a structured `DB health` message containing:\n   - `totalSizeMB` — combined size of all tenant + system databases\n   - `auditSizeMB` — size of the audit database\n   - `tenantCount` — number of registered tenants\n   - `executionRows` / `eventRows` / `auditRows` — total row counts\n   - `oldestUnpurgedDays` — age of the oldest record in days (early warning when data outpaces retention)\n   - `retentionDays` — configured retention for comparison\n\nThis gives operators visibility into database growth every 60 seconds, providing early warning before disk-full or performance degradation occurs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":423,"cache_read_input_tokens":50038,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":423},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5f0d330-c559-491f-855c-57366fc0f3c7","uuid":"81c42e86-0d18-43e1-aaaf-b07288bcdb52"}
